{"id":"11377","name":"ttm.sh (macOS)","tagline":"curl to Tilde.Town’s temporary file share instantaneously.","icon":"ios15 c3980825855 g61456","latest":"32360","description":"\n\t\t\t\t\t<p><img alt=\"ttm.sh Shortcut\" src=\"https://i.snap.as/ineSs5n7.png\"></p>\n<p>This shortcut automates the process of uploading to <a href=\"https://ttm.sh\">The Null Pointer</a> with <code>curl</code> using the first command listed on that landing page, verbatim:</p>\n<p><code>curl -F’file=@Shortcut Input (File Path)’ https://ttm.sh</code></p>\n<p>Here’s <a href=\"https://ttm.sh/iad.43.png\">an example result</a>: <code>https://ttm.sh/iad.43.png</code></p>\n<p>It includes by default an action to save the result in a <a href=\"https://apps.apple.com/us/app/data-jar/id1453273600\">Data Jar</a> specified at install, but this is not required. If you do not intend to use it, you will need to delete the action, though.</p>\n<p>Here’s <a href=\"https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/43663476/159292491-4fd43499-b36a-47e2-b928-51fb4d907731.mov\">a very brief video demo</a>.</p>\n<p><em>For more information on the service, <a href=\"https://tildegit.org/tildeverse/ttm.sh\">see its repository</a>. If you’d like to know more about the Tildeverse, see Paul Ford’s “<a href=\"https://medium.com/message/tilde-club-i-had-a-couple-drinks-and-woke-up-with-1-000-nerds-a8904f0a2ebf\">I had a couple drinks and woke up with 1,000 nerds</a>” and/or <a href=\"https://cgi.tilde.town/users/signup\">come join me on Tilde.Town</a>. :)</em></p>\n<hr>\n<h2>Contact</h2>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"https://davidblue.wtf/db.vcf\">Contact Card</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"https://t.me/extratone\">Telegram</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"mailto:davidblue@extratone.com\">Email</a> </li>\n<li><a href=\"https://twitter.com/NeoYokel\">Twitter</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"https://mastodon.social/@DavidBlue\">Mastodon</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"https://discord.gg/0b9KQUKP858b0iZF\">Discord</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"https://raindrop.io/davidblue/soc